{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Incremental Learning in AIIncremental learning approaches have emerged as a vital solution for enabling artificial intelligence systems to learn from new data without forgetting previously acquired knowledge, when they have proven effective in scenarios where the data distribution changes over time, allowing models to adapt to new patterns and trends [23,24,25].",
    "Incremental learning has also facilitated the reduction of computational resources required for training models on large datasets by focusing on the integration of new information [26,27].",
    "The concept of plasticitystability balance is fundamental in incremental learning, ensuring that the model remains flexible enough to learn new information while retaining important past knowledge [28].",
    "Techniques such as rehearsal and pseudo-rehearsal have been employed to mitigate the effects of catastrophic forgetting, a common challenge in incremental learning scenarios [24,29,30].",
    "Incremental learning algorithms have been designed to efficiently identify and prioritize the most informative and relevant data points for learning [27,31,32,33,34]."
  ],
